---
// COMPONENTS
import InternalHero from "@/components/InternalHero.astro";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Heading from "@/components/Heading.astro";
import SplitOverlay from "@/components/SplitOverlay.astro";
import Links from "@/components/Links.astro";
import CardGrid from "@/components/CardGrid.astro";
import ServicesCard from "@/components/ServicesCard.astro";
import FAQ from "@/components/FAQ.astro";

// IMAGES
import seanLambo from "@/assets/SeanLambo.png";
import garageDoorOpenerHero from "@/assets/garageDoorOpenerHero.jpg";
import closingDoor from "@/assets/closingDoor.png";
import seanGarage from "@/assets/seanGarage.png";
import garageClicker from "@/assets/garageClicker.png";

// ICONS
import quality from "@/assets/quality.svg";
import pricing from "@/assets/pricing.svg";
import available from "@/assets/available.svg";

// DTA
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";
const faq = await getCollection("garageOpenerRepairFAQ");

const faqData = faq.map(item => ({
  tag: item.data.tag,
  question: item.data.question,
  answer: item.data.answer,
}));

const openerRepairProcess = [
  {
    title: "System Diagnosis",
    description:
      "We inspect the opener motor, drive system, sensors, remotes, and door balance to determine the root cause of the problem.",
    icon: quality,
    iconAlt: "System diagnosis icon",
  },
  {
    title: "Repair or Installation",
    description:
      "If the issue can be repaired, we restore the opener using high-quality replacement parts. If replacement is recommended, we install a new system designed for long-term performance.",
    icon: pricing,
    iconAlt: "Repair or installation icon",
  },
  {
    title: "Programming & Safety Testing",
    description:
      "After installation or repair, we program remotes, test safety sensors, verify door balance, and confirm smooth operation.",
    icon: available,
    iconAlt: "Programming and safety testing icon",
  },
];

const serviceSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Service",
  serviceType: "Garage Door Opener Repair",
  provider: {
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    name: "Lambo's Garage Door Service",
  },
  areaServed: ["Franklin County TN", "Coffee County TN"],
};
---

<Layout
  pageTitle="Garage Door Opener Repair in Franklin & Coffee County, TN"
  description="Is your garage door opener not working? We provide professional garage door opener repair in Franklin & Coffee County. Call today."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(serviceSchema)} />

  <InternalHero
    pageTitle="Garage Door Opener Repair in Central Tennessee"
    title="When Your Garage Door Won’t Respond, We Get It Working Again"
    ariaLabel="Garage Door Opener Repair Hero Section"
    imageSrc={garageDoorOpenerHero}
    imageAlt="Garage door opener repair service"
    primaryCtaText="Schedule Garage Door Opener Repair"
    primaryCtaHref="/contact"
    secondaryCtaText="Call Now for Service"
    secondaryCtaHref="tel:+19312229963"
  >
    <p>
      A malfunctioning garage door opener can leave you stuck inside your garage or unable to get
      your vehicle out when you need it most. Whether your opener has stopped responding, your
      remote won’t connect, or you’re ready to upgrade to a modern smart garage system, we diagnose
      the problem quickly and restore dependable operation.
    </p>
    <p>
      We proudly serve homeowners in Winchester, Tullahoma, Lynchburg, Estill Springs, Decherd, and
      surrounding communities across the area.
    </p>
    <div class="btn-wrapper btn-wrapper--left">
      <Links variant="primary" href="/contact">Schedule Garage Door Opener Repair</Links>
      <Links variant="outline" href="tel:+19312229963">Call Now for Service</Links>
    </div>
  </InternalHero>

  <!-- Content for the About Us page goes here -->
  <section class="bg-primary">
    <div class="container container-md">
      <div class="content-md">
        <Heading tag="h2" size="xl" fontFamily="primary" marginBottom="l" weight="fw500"
          >Reliable Garage Door Opener Service You Can Trust</Heading
        >
        <p>
          Garage door openers are responsible for the everyday convenience most homeowners rely on
          without thinking about it. When the opener stops working properly, the entire garage door
          system becomes frustrating or unusable.
        </p>

        <p>
          Across Franklin and Coffee County, homeowners frequently experience opener issues caused
          by worn gears, electrical problems, misaligned sensors, or outdated systems. In some cases
          the opener motor continues running but the door doesn’t move. In others, the remote or
          wall control stops responding entirely.
        </p>

        <p>
          Our goal is to determine whether your opener needs a repair or if a new system would
          provide better long-term reliability.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SplitOverlay
    title="Common Garage Door Opener Problems We Repair"
    imgSrc={seanGarage}
    imgAlt="Sean performing garage door maintenance service"
    background="bg-light"
    orientation="left"
  >
    <p>Most opener issues begin as small inconveniences before becoming larger problems.</p>

    <p><strong>We regularly repair opener systems experiencing:</strong></p>

    <ul>
      <li><p>Garage door opener not responding</p></li>
      <li><p>Remote or keypad not working</p></li>
      <li><p>Wall switch not activating the door</p></li>
      <li><p>Opener motor running but door not moving</p></li>
      <li><p>Loud grinding or humming noises</p></li>
      <li><p>Intermittent door movement</p></li>
      <li><p>Safety sensor alignment issues</p></li>
      <li><p>Slow or inconsistent door operation</p></li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Many of these issues can be resolved with professional repair rather than replacing the entire
      system.
    </p>

    <p>
      If your opener failure is related to broken springs or mechanical damage, our <strong
        ><a href="/garage-door-repair">Garage Door Repair</a></strong
      > service may also be needed to restore full system performance.
    </p>
  </SplitOverlay>

  <SplitOverlay
    title="Modern Garage Door Opener Upgrades"
    imgSrc={garageClicker}
    imgAlt="Garage door remote control"
    background="bg-white"
    orientation="right"
  >
    <p>
      Older garage door openers can still function, but modern systems offer significant
      improvements in reliability, safety, and convenience.
    </p>

    <p>
      Homeowners in Winchester, Tullahoma, and surrounding communities often choose to upgrade their
      opener for features such as:
    </p>

    <Heading tag="h3" size="m" fontFamily="primary" marginBottom="s" weight="fw500"
      >WiFi & Smartphone Control</Heading
    >

    <p>
      Modern openers allow you to control and monitor your garage door directly from your
      smartphone. This provides remote access, activity alerts, and the ability to check whether
      your door is open or closed from anywhere.
    </p>

    <Heading tag="h3" size="m" fontFamily="primary" marginBottom="s" weight="fw500"
      >Quiet Belt-Drive Operation</Heading
    >

    <p>
      Newer belt-drive opener systems operate much more quietly than older chain-drive models,
      making them ideal for homes with attached garages.
    </p>

    <Heading tag="h3" size="m" fontFamily="primary" marginBottom="s" weight="fw500"
      >Battery Backup Systems</Heading
    >

    <p>
      Battery backup options allow your garage door opener to function during power outages,
      ensuring you can still open and close your garage safely.
    </p>

    <Heading tag="h3" size="m" fontFamily="primary" marginBottom="s" weight="fw500"
      >Remote & Keypad Programming</Heading
    >

    <p>
      We set up and program all remotes, wireless keypads, and smart connectivity features so your
      system is ready to use immediately.
    </p>

    <p>
      We install and service all major brands including LiftMaster, Chamberlain, Genie, and
      Craftsman.
    </p>
  </SplitOverlay>

  <SplitOverlay
    title="Repair or Replace? How We Help You Decide"
    imgSrc={seanLambo}
    imgAlt="Photo of Sean and Lambo"
    background="bg-primary"
    orientation="left"
  >
    <p>
      Not every opener problem requires a full replacement. In many cases, repairing worn components
      can restore normal operation.
    </p>

    <p><strong>However, replacement may be the better option if:</strong></p>

    <ul>
      <li><p>The opener motor is severely worn</p></li>
      <li><p>Replacement parts are no longer available</p></li>
      <li><p>The unit lacks modern safety features</p></li>
      <li><p>You want smart connectivity or quieter operation</p></li>
    </ul>

    <p>Our goal is to recommend the solution that makes the most sense for your home and budget.</p>
  </SplitOverlay>

  <section class="bg-light">
    <div class="container container-md column-small">
      <div class="content-md">
        <Heading tag="h2" size="xl" fontFamily="primary" marginBottom="l" weight="fw500">
          Our Garage Door Opener Service Process
        </Heading>
        <p class="margin-bottom-xl">
          We follow a structured process to ensure every opener system operates reliably and safely.
          Most opener repairs and installations can be completed in a single visit.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-full">
        <CardGrid cardData={openerRepairProcess} />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FAQ faq={faqData} />

  <SplitOverlay
    title="Garage Door Service Across Franklin & Coffee County"
    imgSrc={closingDoor}
    imgAlt="Closing a garage door"
    background="bg-light"
    orientation="right"
  >
    <p>
      Lambo’s Garage Door Service proudly provides professional garage door repair, installation,
      and maintenance throughout Franklin County, Coffee County, and surrounding Central Tennessee
      communities.
    </p>

    <p>Because we are based nearby in Estill Springs, we regularly serve homeowners in:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <p><a href="/garage-door-repair-tullahoma-tn">Tullahoma</a></p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p><a href="/garage-door-repair-winchester-tn">Winchester</a></p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p><a href="/garage-door-repair-decherd-tn">Decherd</a></p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p><a href="/garage-door-repair-estill-springs-tn">Estill Springs</a></p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p><a href="/garage-door-repair-lynchburg-tn">Lynchburg</a></p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </SplitOverlay>

  <section>
    <div class="container container-md column-main">
      <div class="content-md">
        <Heading tag="h2" size="xl" fontFamily="primary" marginBottom="l" weight="fw500">
          Explore Our Other Garage Door Services
        </Heading>
        <p class="margin-bottom-xl">
          To keep your entire system operating safely and efficiently, we also provide the following
          services.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-full">
        <div class="services-grid flex">
          <ServicesCard descriptionType="short" excludeIds={[4]} />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
